Package: optsens
Title: Sensitivity Analysis for Regression and IV Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Tobias", "Freidling", , "tobias.freidling@epfl.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0724-4297")),
           person("Qingyuan", "Zhao", role = c("aut")))
Description: Optimization-based sensitivity analysis for unmeasured confounding
    in linear regression and instrumental variable models. Users provide the data and specify
    and specify a sensitivity model. The package estimates the resulting
    partially identified range, computes bootstrap sensitivity intervals and
    provides visualizations of the results. Details can be found in the paper
    by Freidling and Zhao (2024) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2301.00040>.
License: GPL (>= 3)
